\mathbb{Q}(\sqrt{3+2\sqrt{2}})
\mathbb{Q}
3+2\sqrt{2}=2+2\sqrt{2}+1=(\sqrt{2}+1)^2
 \mathbb{Q}(\sqrt{3+2\sqrt{2}})=\mathbb{Q}(\sqrt{2}+1)=\mathbb{Q}(\sqrt{2}) 
\ 3 + 2\sqrt{2}\ 
\ (3+2\sqrt{2})\:(3-2\sqrt{2})\ =\ 9 - 4\cdot 2\ =\ 1
\rm\:\color{blue}{subtracting\ out}\ \sqrt{norm}\ = \pm1\ 
\rm\ 3 + 2\sqrt{2}\: -\: \pm1\  =\  2 + 2\sqrt{2}\ \ or\ \ 4 + 2\sqrt{2} 
\rm\qquad \sqrt{trace(2+2\sqrt{2})}\ =\ \sqrt{4}\ =\ 2,\quad\ \ so\ \quad\ \color{brown}{dividing\ it\ out}\ \ \ (2+2\sqrt{2})/2\ =\  1+\sqrt{2}
\rm\qquad \sqrt{trace(4+2\sqrt{2})}\ =\ \sqrt{8}\ =\  2\sqrt{2}\quad so\quad \color{brown}{dividing\ it\ out}\ \ \ (4+2\sqrt{2})/(2\sqrt{2})\: =\: \sqrt{2}+1
\rm\ (1 + \sqrt{2})^2\ =\ 3 + 2\sqrt{2}\:.\ 
