(X^2 -3)^2 -8 = X^4 -6X^2 + 1
\mathbb Q
\frac rs \in \mathbb Q
(r,s) = 1
r|1
s|1
\pm1
 \begin{align} X^4 - 6X^2 + 1 &= (X^2 + aX \pm 1)(X^2 + cX \pm 1) \\ &= X^4 + (a+c)X^3 + (ac\pm 2)X^2 \pm (a+c)X + 1 \end{align} 
a = -c
-6 = ac \pm 2 = -a^2 \pm 2
a = 2
c=-2
\pm 1
X^4 - 6X^2 + 1 = (X^2 + 2X - 1)(X^2 - 2X - 1)
\mathbb Q
\mathbb Q
\sqrt{3+2\sqrt{2}}
[\mathbb Q(\sqrt{3+2\sqrt{2}}):\mathbb Q] = 2
\mathbb{Q}\subset \mathbb{Q}(\sqrt2)\subset \mathbb{Q}\left(\sqrt{3+2\sqrt2}\right)
\leq 2
\left(\sqrt{3+2\sqrt2}\right)^2=3+2\sqrt2\in \mathbb{Q}(\sqrt2)
a,b\in \mathbb{Q}
\sqrt{3+2\sqrt2}=a+b\sqrt2
3+2\sqrt2=a^2+2b\sqrt2+2b^2
b=1
a=1
\sqrt{3+2\sqrt2}=1+\sqrt2
\left\lvert\mathbb{Q}\left(\sqrt{3+2\sqrt2}\right):\mathbb{Q}(\sqrt2)\right\rvert=1
\left\lvert \mathbb{Q}\left(\sqrt{3+2\sqrt2}\right):\mathbb{Q}\right\rvert=2
